# Commit Message Convention

When generating commit messages, always follow this prefix mapping:

- `feat:` when adding a new user-facing feature.
- `fix:` when fixing an existing bug.
- `docs:` when only documentation files change (README, guides, docs) and no code logic changes.
- `style:` when only formatting/styling changes are made (whitespace, commas, formatting) with no logic changes.
- `refactor:` when restructuring or optimizing existing code without adding features or fixing bugs.

## Requirements

- Output format must be: `<type>: <short summary>`
- Keep summary concise and specific.
- Choose exactly one type based on the primary intent of the changes.
- Do not use other prefixes unless explicitly requested by the user.

## Examples

- `feat: add venue search by coordinates`
- `fix: handle null response in team creation flow`
- `docs: update setup steps for backend environment variables`
- `style: format venues page styles and align spacing`
- `refactor: extract venue scoring logic into helper function`
